commit.message: Set version to 4.3.4 and update Changelog

Fix manpage Host:Port part

Reported at https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=858262

Fix stack smash in lmove.c and suckutils.c

The switch to using -fstack-protector-strong in Debian stretch has exposed a
stack-smashing bug: https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=832265

The problem affects 64-bit platforms, as the code is assuming
sizeof(pid_t) == sizeof(long), yet on x86_64:

sizeof(pid_t) == 4
sizeof(long) == 8

The relevant code is in suckutils.c, do_lockfile():

int do_lockfile(PMaster master) {
...
    pid_t pid;
...
        fscanf(f_lock, "%ld", (long *) &pid);
...
}

This writes an 8-byte long to the location of the 4-byte pid variable,
smashing 4 bytes of the stack.

I doubt this is usefully exploitable (with the stack protector enabled,
it's only overwriting the canary), but it does mean a stale lockfile
causes suck to crash (but helpfully, the lockfile is unlinked before the
crash, so the next run will be successful).

Author: ksherlock@gmail.com

Return if no host provided to connect_to_nntphost

If no host is provided to `connect_to_nntphost` return early.
Previously, it would strdup(NULL) which is illegal and can cause a SIGSEGV.

This fixes some, if not all, of the Mayhem bugs reported to Debian:

- https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=716448
- https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=716510
- https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=716606
